article.headline: Rutgers manhandles Oregon State
article.linkText: Rutgers blasts Oregon State at Paradise Jam
article.story:
CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Chelsea Newton
scored 16 points to lead Rutgers (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today; No. 17 AP) to a 77-53 victory over
Oregon State in the second round of the Paradise Jam tournament on
Friday.

Kim Butler led Oregon State (1-2) with 17 points and 10
rebounds.

Rutgers (3-0) held a six-point lead at the break and limited
Oregon State to just 18 points in the second half.

Oregon State squandered a 17-point first-half lead against
Kentucky in the opening round. Rutgers beat South Dakota 68-50 in
its opener.
